      {
        "id": "1f05d5b1-2f00-4d3d-8086-cdea6d522e86",
        "page_slug": "about",
        "type": "rich_text",
        "display_order": 1,
        "data": {
          "heading": "Two bankers walk into a coffee shop",
          "body_markdown": "Tom and Cat spent years in mortgage banking before deciding the world needed one more genuinely good neighborhood coffee shop more than it needed two more bankers. Trouble Brewing is the result — a warm, art-filled room in the heart of Haddon Heights where the coffee is serious and the vibe is not."
        },
        "draft_data": null,
        "status": "published",
        "visible": true,
        "updated_at": "2026-07-13T16:07:29.386674+00:00"
      },
      {
        "id": "709a390e-8eab-4bcd-8db5-85bbc38c0a2d",
        "page_slug": "about",
        "type": "rich_text",
        "display_order": 2,
        "data": {
          "heading": "Why La Colombe",
          "body_markdown": "We partnered with **La Colombe** because great coffee shouldn't be complicated — it should be consistent, ethical, and delicious. That partnership is the foundation we build every drink on."
        },
        "draft_data": null,
        "status": "published",
        "visible": true,
        "updated_at": "2026-07-13T16:07:29.386674+00:00"
      },
      {
        "id": "3bc8651d-9089-4195-b595-8ba3412a5f21",
        "page_slug": "about",
        "type": "rich_text",
        "display_order": 3,
        "data": {
          "heading": "Why local matters",
          "body_markdown": "Independent shops are the connective tissue of a town. We buy local where we can, host our neighbors, and try to send everyone back out the door a little more caffeinated and a little more cared-for."
        },
        "draft_data": null,
        "status": "published",
        "visible": true,
        "updated_at": "2026-07-13T16:07:29.386674+00:00"
      },
